    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-05-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-05-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="65"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d65">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_SS1">S/S</gloss>–<gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> files,
                    lot 66 D 148, “Solarium”</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum for the Record by the Special Assistant to the
                        President for National Security Affairs (<persName corresp="#p_CUTLERR1"
                            >Cutler</persName>)</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d65fn1">Copy to <persName corresp="#p_SMITHGWB1">Walter
                            Bedell Smith</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Personal and Confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-05-15">15 May
                            1953</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list rend="flushleft" type="subject">
                    <item>Subject:</item>
                    <item>Solarium Project</item>
                </list>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>This memorandum is an initial report by the Working Committee of the
                        National Security Council appointed to arrange the detailed plans for
                        carrying out the above project (The Acting Secretary of State, <persName
                            corresp="#p_SMITHGWB1">General W. B. Smith</persName>; the Director for
                        Central Intelligence, <persName corresp="#p_DULLESAW1">Allen W.
                            Dulles</persName>; and the Special Assistant to the President for
                        National Security Affairs, <persName corresp="#p_CUTLERR1">Robert
                            Cutler</persName>.)</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>In accordance with the President’s instructions, as reported to the
                        Council on 15 May 1953,<note n="2" xml:id="d65fn2">The Presidential
                            instructions under reference cannot be further identified.</note> the
                        following have been requested to act as the Panel to draft precise and
                        detailed terms of reference for each alternative (see par 2a, Solarium
                        Project Memo of 9 May 1953<note n="3" xml:id="d65fn3">For text, see <ref
                                target="#pg_323">p. 323</ref>.</note>), and have accepted the
                        assignment: <list>
                            <item>General <persName>James H. Doolittle</persName>, <hi rend="italic"
                                    >Chairman</hi>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <persName corresp="#p_AMORYRJ1">Robert Amory, Jr.</persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LEMNITZERLGLL1">Lt. General L. L.
                                    Lemnitzer</persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <persName>Dean Rusk</persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>Admiral <persName>Leslie C. Stevens</persName>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <pb facs="0358" n="328" xml:id="pg_328"/>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>The Panel will convene in Room 376, Executive Offices Building,
                        Washington, D.C. on Monday, 25 May 1953, at 9:30 A.M. o’clock. The members
                        of the Working Committee will discuss the problem with the Panel at 10:30
                        A.M. o’clock.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>It is anticipated that the Panel will carry on their work continuously
                        until completion, which it is anticipated should be not later than 1 June
                        1953. Office space, secretarial assistance, required source materials, etc.,
                        will be provided in the National Security Council Area. Mr. <persName>T. M.
                            Koons</persName>, <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Special Staff
                        Member (Executive 3–7491, Extension 3675), will act as Executive Secretary
                        for Solarium Project.</item>
                    <label>5.</label>
                    <item>No publicity of any kind should be given to, or mention made of, the
                        project. It is essential to success that the most complete discretion be
                        observed. For that reason, no further communication will be sent from this
                        office. If communication regarding the above arrangements is necessary,
                        please telephone to the undersigned or Mr. <persName>Koons</persName>
                        (referring only to Solarium).</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CUTLERR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Cutler</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
